Units tvDMXREP and INPUTWIN
===========================

Unit tvDMXREP:
-------------

    The procedures and objects in this unit will output a report from
    the data in a tvDMX view.


The reporting objects:

  object TDmxReport

    This is the base reporting object.  It has an abstract Print() method
    and will not function as-is.


  object TDmxReportFile

    Overrides TDmxReport's Print() method to output to a file.


  object TDmxReportStream

    Overrides TDmxReport's Print() method to output to a stream.


  object TDmxReportHexFile

    Overrides TDmxReportFile's RecNumStr() method to return a record
    number as a hexadecimal address.  This object is defined in unit
    tvDMXHEX.PAS.


  Each object is initialized by its Init() constructor, and executed by a
  Run() method.  Reports can be customized by overriding virtual methods.


  Where to override sections of the printed page:

	  AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAA
	  BBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBB
	  CCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCC
	  DDDDDDEEEEEE.................FFFFFF
	  DDDDDDEEEEEE.................FFFFFF
	  DDDDDDEEEEEE.................FFFFFF
	  DDDDDDEEEEEE.................FFFFFF
	  DDDDDDEEEEEE.................FFFFFF
	  DDDDDDEEEEEE.................FFFFFF
	  DDDDDDEEEEEE.................FFFFFF
	  DDDDDDEEEEEE.................FFFFFF
	  GGGGGGGGGGGGGGGGGGGGGGGGGGGGGGGGGGG
	  HHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHH


   [.]--data records as formatted by the tvDMX view.

    A --processed by procedure SetupPage() and by evCommand cmPRN_NewPage*.
	The default method does nothing.

    B --processed by procedure PrintLabels().
	This method outputs the DMX field header labels.

    C --processed by procedure SetupDMX().
	Processes a line to appear under the field header labels.

    D --processed by procedure SetupLine().
	The default method does nothing.

    E --outputs a string returned from RecNumStr(CurrentRecord).  Function
	RecNumStr() returns the result from func TDmxScroller.RecNumStr().
	This string is used only if line numbers are enabled.

    F --processed by procedure EndLine().
	This method outputs a line-feed.

    G --processed by procedure EndDMX().
	Processes a line to appear under the field header labels.

    H --processed by procedure EndPage() and by evCommand cmPRN_EndPage*.
	This method outputs a page-feed.

  * The cmPRN_NewPage and cmPRN_EndPage command events are sent to the main
    Application view and to the view being processed so that their event-
    handlers may print additional text specific to those views without
    having to create a new TDmxReport descendant.  Event.InfoPtr will be a
    PDmxReport pointer type which can be used to print the text like this:

      PDmxReport (Event.InfoPtr)^.PrintStr ('Sample text.');
      PDmxReport (Event.InfoPtr)^.NewLine;

    To ensure proper formatting, use the TDmxReport.NewLine method as shown,
    instead of adding carriage return codes to the text in the PrintStr()
    statement.  Also see procedures PrnPageStart() and PrnPageEnd().


  Report objects could be instantiated and run by themselves, but procedure
  DmxReportBox() can be used to execute them from within a message box:

  procedure DmxReportBox (ATitle :TTitleStr; Msg :string; Report :PDmxReport);

    Parameters: ATitle --window title;
		Msg    --message string to be displayed during printing;
		Report --report object, initialized and ready to run
			 (this is disposed after the procedure is done).

  Example:

  DmxReportBox ('Working', 'Processing report...'^M^M^C'to "FILE"',
		New (PDmxReportFile, Init (DMX, '|', TRUE, 50,78, 'FILE')));

	 'Working' --window title;
	    DMX    --a tvDMX view object;
	    '|'    --replacement delimiter for visible delimiters
		     above #126  (uses given delimiters if #0 is used);
	    TRUE   --display record numbers;
	    50     --number of records per page;
	    78     --width of each page;
	    'FILE' --report filename.

    How to print data in the current window:

      procedure PrintCurrentWindow;
      var  DMX  : PDmxScroller;
      begin
	DMX := Message (DeskTop, evCommand, cmDMX_RollCall, @Self);
	If (DMX <> nil) then
	  begin
	  DmxReportBox ('Printing', 'Processing report...'^M^M^C'to "PRN"',
		New (PDmxReportFile, Init (DMX, '|', TRUE, 50,78, 'PRN')));
	  end;
      end;

    Use procedure PrnCurrentDMX() if you are also using PrnSetOptions()
    (see below).


			   < Optional Equipment >

  function  StdPrnMenuItems (AHelpCtx : word;  Next : PMenuItem): PMenuItem;

    Creates a chain of menu items for "Settings", "Line feed", "Form feed"
    and "Reset" command options.  The last three commands are handled by
    the TAppPrn object's event-handler.  If AHelpCtx is not zero, then the
    individual help context will increment for each item.


  procedure PrnCurrentDMX;

    Prints the current window, using the parameters set by the "Settings"
    dialog box.  See procedure PrnSetOptions().


  procedure PrnPageStart (var Event : TEvent);
  procedure PrnPageEnd (var Event : TEvent);

    These procedures would normally be called by your main application's
    event-handler to print additional information related to the window.

      PrnPageStart() --prints the window's title if it has one;
      PrnPageEnd()   --prints the current page number.

    The Event parameter should be the one given to the Application's
    event-handler.


  function  PrnSetOptions (AHelpCtx,AOKCtx,ACancelCtx : word) : word;

    This procedure opens a dialog box with output options for the end-user.

    Parameters: AHelpCtx   --first help context number;
                AOKCtx     --help context for OK button;
                ACancelCtx --help context for Cancel button.

    Result:	This function returns the command used to exit this window
		--cmOK or cmCancel.

      AHelpCtx will be used this way:

	AHelpCtx+0 = 'Destination: Printer'
	AHelpCtx+1 = 'Destination: File'
	AHelpCtx+2 = 'Destination: (Enter filename)'
	AHelpCtx+3 = 'Options: Allow extended characters'
	AHelpCtx+4 = 'Options: Display record numbers'
	AHelpCtx+5 = 'Options: Line feed on carriage return'
	AHelpCtx+6 = 'Options: Manual page feed'
	AHelpCtx+7 = 'Page Length'
	AHelpCtx+8 = 'Page Width'

    Notes:  function StdPrnMenuItems() will generate a menu item for this
    procedure with the command cmPRN_SetOptions, but your main application
    must still handle the event.  Example:

    Case Event.Command of
      ...
      cmPRN_SetOptions:  PrnSetOptions (hcSetOptions, hcOK, hcCancel);
      ...

Unit INPUTWIN:
-------------

    This unit is designed to place a small field-window over most fields
    (except for BOOLEAN and 'N' dBASE-types).  Users can use this window
    to override READ-ONLY or case restrictions, and to enter numbers not
    in the range allowed by a field's template.

    Calculations may be entered if the field is numeric.  Example:

      (341.6*92.1)+5


  procedure CalcVal (S : string; var V : trealnum; var code : integer);

    This procedure works like procedure Val() --with similar syntax--
    but it will also perform calculations.  The '+','-','*','/' and '^'
    operators may be used.  Commas are not permitted.  Error positions
    are returned in the parameter "code".  Although this procedure was
    designed for object FieldWin, it can also be used independently.


  procedure CurrentFieldWindow;

    Opens a FieldWin box over the current field in the current window.
    Nothing happens if the current window is not a tvDMX window or if
    the field cannot be edited by FieldWin.


  object TEditField  =  OBJECT (TInputLine)

    This view displays a TInputLine which the user can edit.
    Its Valid(Command) method will get the current field's data when
    Command=cmValid, and then return the data when Command=cmOK if
    the string can be returned in that field's type.  It uses CalcVal()
    to convert the entered string into a number if necessary.
    The constructor's only parameter is a PDmxEditor pointer.  This may
    be changed in future versions.


  object TFieldWin   =  OBJECT (TDialog)

    This dialog box positions itself over the currently selected field
    of a given PDmxEditor view.  The only other parameter is the window's
    title.  ValidView() absolutely must be called before inserting this
    window into the desktop to prevent its use on BOOLEAN or 'N' fields.
    Procedure CurrentFieldWindow() will manage this window automatically.


